WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.403 --> 00:00:05.171
Barclays Online Banking

2
00:00:05.171 --> 00:00:08.174
How to report a lost or stolen debit card

3
00:00:09.409 --> 00:00:14.080
It's easy to report your card lost or
stolen with Barclays Online Banking.

4
00:00:14.214 --> 00:00:20.286
Start by clicking 'Report damaged, lost or stolen card'
from the quick links section

5
00:00:20.620 --> 00:00:23.456
or by going to the 'Manage accounts' tab.

6
00:00:23.456 --> 00:00:29.295
Then select 'Report a damaged, lost or stolen card'
from the 'Card services' section.

7
00:00:29.496 --> 00:00:31.798
Select the account your card is on

8
00:00:31.798 --> 00:00:34.567
and if you have more than one card
on that account

9
00:00:34.567 --> 00:00:37.437
choose the one that's
missing so we can block it.

10
00:00:37.437 --> 00:00:40.440
Then tell us if the card was lost or stolen.

11
00:00:41.074 --> 00:00:43.943
Now tell us the country where the card went missing.

12
00:00:44.477 --> 00:00:45.845
The city or town

13
00:00:45.845 --> 00:00:48.415
and an approximate location.

14
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:50.784
Select a date and time

15
00:00:54.587 --> 00:00:58.058
and if your PIN is known by anyone other than yourself.

16
00:00:58.324 --> 00:01:04.330
Check through the information you've entered
and if you're happy, click on 'Block card now'.

17
00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:07.600
Now that your card has been
reported as lost or stolen

18
00:01:07.600 --> 00:01:10.370
select if you'd like to order a replacement card.

19
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:13.206
Check your delivery address is correct.

20
00:01:13.206 --> 00:01:14.774
Click 'Next'.

21
00:01:15.408 --> 00:01:19.345
Check your details and click
on 'Confirm new card order'.

22
00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:23.817
Your new card is on its way and will
be with you within five working days.

